Template: mico-marmotta/title
Type: title
Description: MICO Marmotta Configuration

Template: mico-marmotta/database-name
Type: string
Default: marmotta
Description: Name of PostgreSQL database to use for Marmotta:
 Configure the name of the database to use for Marmotta. In case the database does not exist, the setup script allows
 to automatically create it (select "Yes" in the respective question). Marmotta will automatically create its tables
 when starting up.

Template: mico-marmotta/database-host
Type: string
Description: PostgreSQL server host name:
 Provide the host name or IP address (and optionally the port) of the PostgreSQL server to be used by 
 Apache Marmotta to store its data.

Template: mico-marmotta/create-database
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Create Marmotta database and user?
 The setup script can automatically create the PostgreSQL database and user configured in
 the previous steps.
 .
 If you choose not to create the database, the setup script will only update
 the Marmotta configuration with the values
 you provided; in this case you need to make sure the database exists and is accessible.

Template: mico-marmotta/host-name
Type: string
Description: Server host name:
 Provide the host name or IP address this server will be accessed with. This setting is important for Marmotta to
 create the correct resource URLs.

